---
---

<section id="power-users" class="py-24 px-4 sm:px-6 bg-[#1c1c27]">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">

    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-start justify-between gap-12 mb-16">
      <div class="flex-1">
        <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-[#a78bfa] pl-6 mb-16">
          <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-lg italic leading-relaxed">
            "Engram <span class="not-italic font-semibold text-[#f0f0f5]">/ˈɛnɡram/</span> — a hypothetical means by which memory traces are stored as biophysical or biochemical changes in the brain. First named by Richard Semon, 1904.<br /><br /><span class="not-italic font-semibold text-[#f0f0f5]">Graphnosis calls its multi-graph a</span> <span class="not-italic font-semibold text-[#a78bfa]">Graphnosis Engram</span><span class="not-italic text-[#f0f0f5]">.</span>"
          </p>
        </blockquote>

        <div class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black text-white">
            Your Cortex. Your rules.
          </h2>
        </div>

        <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
          Each engram in Graphnosis is an independent encrypted memory space — your work projects, personal notes, research, health records. Separate graphs, separate keys, separate rules. Your AI draws from the right one automatically.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center md:pt-4">
        <img src="/graphnosis-logo-transparent-bg.png" alt="Graphnosis" class="w-80 h-80 opacity-90" />
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- What the graph stores -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-6">What gets indexed inside an engram</h3>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

        <article class="bg-[#13131a] border border-[#2a2a3d] rounded-xl p-6 flex flex-col gap-3">
          <a href="/getting-started/overview" class="text-base font-bold text-white hover:text-[#67e8f9] transition-colors">Temporal awareness ↗</a>
          <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base leading-relaxed mb-3">Every memory node tracks five temporal properties:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1.5">
            {[
              ['createdAt', 'when the knowledge was first ingested'],
              ['lastAccessedAt', 'when it was last retrieved in a query'],
              ['accessCount', 'how many times it has been used'],
              ['validUntil', 'optional expiration for superseded information'],
              ['confidence', '0–1 score that decays over time if knowledge is not reinforced'],
            ].map(([name, desc]) => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm">
                <code class="text-[#67e8f9] font-mono shrink-0 mt-0.5">{name}</code>
                <span class="text-[#c4c6d6]">{desc}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="bg-[#13131a] border border-[#2a2a3d] rounded-xl p-6 flex flex-col gap-3">
          <a href="/guides/graphs-and-tiers" class="text-base font-bold text-white hover:text-[#67e8f9] transition-colors">Contradiction detection ↗</a>
          <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base leading-relaxed">When new content conflicts with existing memory, Graphnosis flags it instead of silently overwriting. The <code class="text-[#67e8f9] font-mono text-sm">contradicts</code> edge type records the conflict with provenance; <code class="text-[#67e8f9] font-mono text-sm">supersedes</code> marks when new information replaces old. You decide what the ground truth is.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="bg-[#13131a] border border-[#2a2a3d] rounded-xl p-6 flex flex-col gap-3 md:col-span-2">
          <a href="/guides/graphs-and-tiers" class="text-base font-bold text-white hover:text-[#67e8f9] transition-colors">Relationship edges — the dual graph ↗</a>
          <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">Both directed and undirected edges exist over the same node set. This dual structure gives AI richer reasoning paths than either graph type alone.</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[#f0f0f5] mb-2">Directed (A → B)</p>
              <ul class="space-y-1.5">
                {[
                  ['contains', 'a section contains a paragraph; also: located-in for geographic membership'],
                  ['precedes', 'one fact or event follows another in time or sequence'],
                  ['cites', 'one source references another; also: wrote / authored, cited-in'],
                  ['defines', 'a definition explains a concept'],
                  ['summarizes', 'a note distills a longer source'],
                  ['causes / supports / contradicts', 'causal and logical relationships'],
                  ['depends-on', 'one fact requires another; also: lives-in, based-in (person → place)'],
                  ['supersedes', 'new information replaces old'],
                  ['discussed-in', 'knowledge traced to conversation origin; also: mentioned-in'],
                  ['knows / works-with / reports-to', 'person-to-person relationships'],
                  ['collaborated-on', 'works-at / founded / member-of / leads — person → org or project'],
                  ['prefers', 'a person favors an approach, tool, or option'],
                ].map(([name, desc]) => (
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm">
                    <code class="text-[#67e8f9] font-mono shrink-0 mt-0.5 leading-relaxed">{name}</code>
                    <span class="text-[#c4c6d6]">{desc}</span>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[#f0f0f5] mb-2">Undirected (A ↔ B)</p>
              <ul class="space-y-1.5">
                {[
                  ['similar-to', 'two facts share vocabulary (TF-IDF cosine similarity)'],
                  ['shares-entity', 'two facts mention the same person, place, or concept'],
                  ['shares-topic', 'two facts belong to the same topic cluster; also: same-topic in the picker'],
                  ['co-occurs', 'two facts appear in the same section or source passage'],
                  ['same-source', 'two facts ingested from the same source file'],
                  ['same-person', 'two mentions of the same person across sources'],
                  ['related-to', 'general association — partners-with, related (fallback for all other cases)'],
                ].map(([name, desc]) => (
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm">
                    <code class="text-[#67e8f9] font-mono shrink-0 mt-0.5">{name}</code>
                    <span class="text-[#c4c6d6]">{desc}</span>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="border-t border-[#2a2a3d] pt-4 mt-4">
            <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base leading-relaxed">
              Switch on the optional <span class="text-[#a78bfa] font-semibold">Graphnosis Neural Network</span> and a third layer of predicted edges joins the same nodes — connections the deterministic passes never recorded, kept apart in a separate <code class="text-[#a78bfa] font-mono">.gnn</code> overlay. The dual-graph becomes a triple-graph. And because recall, consolidation, and cross-engram links all federate across every engram you've granted, the whole Cortex behaves as one multi-graph system — the structure your AI reasons over.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

      </div>

      <article class="bg-[#13131a] border border-[#2a2a3d] rounded-xl p-8 mt-8 flex flex-col gap-6">
        <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">Cross-client persistence</h4>
        <p class="text-[#a0a0b8] text-lg leading-relaxed">Memory persists across every AI client and data source that connects to Graphnosis. What you tell Claude Desktop is available in Cursor. What you ingested from Slack last week is there in Zed today. Sessions don't exist — context does.</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-mono tracking-widest text-[#555570] uppercase mb-4">AI Clients</p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
              {['Claude Desktop', 'Claude Code', 'Cursor', 'Zed', 'GitHub Copilot', 'Any MCP-aware tool'].map(client => (
                <span class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#2a2a3d] text-[#f0f0f5] text-sm font-semibold">{client}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-mono tracking-widest text-[#555570] uppercase mb-4">Data Connectors</p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
              {[
                { label: 'Slack',             color: '#4A154B' },
                { label: 'GitHub',            color: '#238636' },
                { label: 'Linear',            color: '#5E6AD2' },
                { label: 'Trello',            color: '#0052CC' },
                { label: 'RSS',               color: '#F97316' },
                { label: 'Obsidian',          color: '#7C3AED' },
                { label: 'GBrain',            color: '#0EA5E9' },
                { label: 'Webhook',           color: '#67e8f9' },
                { label: 'AI Context Files',  color: '#D97757' },
                { label: 'OPC-UA',            color: '#f59e0b' },
                { label: 'Modbus',            color: '#f59e0b' },
                { label: 'ROS Topics',        color: '#ef4444' },
                { label: 'LoRaWAN',           color: '#84cc16' },
                { label: 'Serial / USB',      color: '#94a3b8' },
              ].map(({ label, color }) => (
                <span
                  class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border text-sm font-semibold"
                  style={`border-color: ${color}44; color: ${color};`}
                >{label}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[#3d3d55] mt-6 text-center" style="font-size:10px; line-height:1.5;">
          All other product names, trademarks, and registered trademarks are the property of their respective owners.
          Graphnosis is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by any third party.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <!-- MCP tools -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black text-white text-center mb-4">What AI cloud and local clients can do with Graphnosis...</h2>
      <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
        All <span class="text-[#f0f0f5] font-semibold">35 MCP tools</span> across 9 functional categories. The deterministic + approximate sets work out of the box;
        the conditional and non-deterministic sets use the optional local LLM (or Neural Network). Every call is visible in the audit log.
        Click any tool for parameters, return shape, and example prompts.
      </p>

      {[
        {
          color: '#67e8f9',
          label: 'Core memory',
          determinism: 'Deterministic · the default',
          desc: 'Reproducible and auditable — identical input, identical result, no AI model required.',
          tools: [
            { name: 'recall', desc: 'Surface relevant context for the current prompt' },
            { name: 'remind', desc: 'Alias for recall — responds to "remind me about X"' },
            { name: 'remember', desc: 'Save a new fact or note to your graph' },
            { name: 'forget', desc: 'Soft-delete a source and every node derived from it' },
            { name: 'apply', desc: 'Commit a reviewed correction diff to the graph' },
            { name: 'stats', desc: 'Inspect engram inventory, node counts, sources' },
            { name: 'vitality', desc: '0–100 score of how alive and well-connected memory is' },
          ],
        },
        {
          color: '#67e8f9',
          label: 'Engram discovery',
          determinism: 'Deterministic · navigation',
          desc: 'Lets the AI find its way around your cortex without guessing names.',
          tools: [
            { name: 'list_engrams', desc: 'Every engram with tier + source counts' },
            { name: 'suggest_engram', desc: 'Best engram to save a note into' },
            { name: 'browse_engram', desc: 'Sources inside one engram, newest first' },
            { name: 'recent', desc: 'Most recently ingested sources across all engrams' },
            { name: 'get_engram_schema', desc: 'Metadata for one engram (tier, template, name)' },
          ],
        },
        {
          color: '#67e8f9',
          label: 'Structured recall',
          determinism: 'Deterministic · advanced',
          desc: 'Variants of recall for when the AI needs more than a prose context block.',
          tools: [
            { name: 'recall_structured', desc: 'Recall returned as a JSON array of node objects' },
            { name: 'recall_with_citations', desc: 'Recall with inline source citation per fact' },
            { name: 'compare_engrams', desc: 'Same query against two engrams, side-by-side' },
            { name: 'cross_search', desc: 'Federated recall over a hand-picked subset' },
          ],
        },
        {
          color: '#67e8f9',
          label: 'Source operations',
          determinism: 'Deterministic · op-log primitives',
          desc: 'Act on a whole saved source — file, URL, clip. All recoverable.',
          tools: [
            { name: 'find_source', desc: 'Keyword substring search across source IDs / refs' },
            { name: 'recall_source', desc: 'Full content of one source, in ingestion order' },
            { name: 'transfer_source', desc: 'Move a source from one engram to another' },
          ],
        },
        {
          color: '#67e8f9',
          label: 'Engram operations',
          determinism: 'Deterministic · bulk',
          desc: 'Engram-level moves and consolidations.',
          tools: [
            { name: 'ingest_batch', desc: 'Save up to 20 notes in one call, each routed' },
            { name: 'engram_summary', desc: 'Readable snapshot — counts + node previews' },
          ],
        },
        {
          color: '#67e8f9',
          label: 'Brain maintenance',
          determinism: 'Deterministic · brain windows',
          desc: 'Read-only views into the autonomous brain engine + consent gate.',
          tools: [
            { name: 'duplicate_pairs', desc: 'Near-duplicate pairs the brain flagged for review' },
            { name: 'healing_journal', desc: 'Audit log of autonomous corrections the brain made' },
            { name: 'gnn_status', desc: 'Neural Network state + predicted-edge count' },
            { name: 'confirm_data_access', desc: 'Headless-fallback consent for sensitive engrams' },
          ],
        },
        {
          color: '#a78bfa',
          label: 'Approximate',
          determinism: 'Vector similarity · no LLM',
          desc: 'Similarity scans across the cortex — deterministic given the embedding state.',
          tools: [
            { name: 'audit_memory', desc: 'Detect near-duplicate content across engrams' },
            { name: 'check_duplicate', desc: 'Pre-flight check before remember — anything similar?' },
          ],
        },
        {
          color: '#a78bfa',
          label: 'Conditional',
          determinism: 'Deterministic by default · LLM-aware',
          desc: 'Deterministic when no LLM/GNN is enabled; richer multi-edit diff when they are.',
          tools: [
            { name: 'edit', desc: 'Propose a structured diff — correction, update, or append — user-approved before any write' },
          ],
        },
        {
          color: '#a78bfa',
          label: 'Non-deterministic',
          determinism: 'Local LLM required · opt-in',
          desc: 'Retrieval stays deterministic; the local LLM (Ollama) produces the prose, so output varies between runs. Off by default.',
          tools: [
            { name: 'develop', desc: 'Draft a strategic plan grounded in your memory' },
            { name: 'predict', desc: 'Risks and opportunities before you act' },
            { name: 'insights', desc: 'Patterns, gaps, conflicts surfaced by the background loop' },
            { name: 'gnn_neighbors', desc: 'Neural Network–predicted related nodes' },
            { name: 'llm_query', desc: 'Local-LLM synthesised answer grounded in recall' },
            { name: 'llm_distill', desc: 'Local-LLM fact extraction — ready for ingest_batch' },
          ],
        },
      ].map((cat) => (
        <div class="mb-8">
          <div class="mb-4">
            <p class="text-sm font-mono tracking-widest uppercase mb-2" style={`color:${cat.color};`}>{cat.label} · <span class="opacity-70">{cat.determinism}</span></p>
            <p class="text-base text-[#c4c6d6]">{cat.desc}</p>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
            {cat.tools.map((tool) => (
              <a
                href="/reference/mcp-tools"
                class="bg-[#13131a] border border-[#2a2a3d] rounded-lg p-5 flex flex-col gap-2.5 transition-colors group"
                style={`--hover-border:${cat.color};`}
                onmouseover="this.style.borderColor=this.style.getPropertyValue('--hover-border')+'66'"
                onmouseout="this.style.borderColor=''"
              >
                <code class="text-base font-mono font-bold" style={`color:${cat.color};`}>{tool.name}</code>
                <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-sm leading-relaxed">{tool.desc}</p>
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}

      <p class="text-base text-[#a0a0b8] mt-10">
        <code class="text-[#67e8f9] font-mono text-base">edit</code> is deterministic by default — it returns a diff for review, and nothing is written until you approve it in the app; the optional Neural Network or local LLM can widen it. <code class="text-[#67e8f9] font-mono text-base">forget</code> is a soft delete — nodes stay recoverable from the op-log. Full reference: <a href="/reference/mcp-tools" class="text-[#67e8f9] hover:underline">/reference/mcp-tools</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Cortex callout -->
    <div class="border-l-4 border-[#a78bfa] bg-[#13131a] rounded-r-xl p-6 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center justify-between gap-6">
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-[#a78bfa] mb-2">Graphnosis Cortex</p>
        <p class="text-[#f0f0f5] font-semibold text-lg leading-snug max-w-lg">
          The premium layer — multi-engram federation, advanced policy controls, and priority recall across all your graphs simultaneously. Every engram remains encrypted, local, and yours.
        </p>
      </div>
      <a
        href="/getting-started/overview"
        class="shrink-0 inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-full border border-[#a78bfa] text-[#a78bfa] hover:bg-[#a78bfa]/10 font-semibold text-sm transition-colors whitespace-nowrap"
      >
        Learn about Graphnosis Cortex
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
